CONDITIONAL STATEMENT :
-- To make the set of instructions(block of code)(conditional block) execute only when the given condition is true.
-- used to decide whether the code has to be executed or skip based on the given condition.
-- line-line(sequence)

BLOCK OF CODE : set of instructions
-- it will execute only when that specific condition is true
CONDITION : An expression that evaluates an result (t/f)
EX : console.log(5>6)

METHODS :
 if-else
Else if 
Switch
Ternary operator

EX: Condition is true 
        let a=5;
        let b=10;
        if(a<b){
            document.write("hi divya","<br>")
        }
        document.write("welcome to india") 

O/P : hi divya
          welcome to india


EX: Condition is false
        let a=5;
        let b=10;
        if(a>b){
            document.write("hi divya","<br>")
        }
        document.write("welcome to india") 
O/P :
 welcome to india
 

EX : IF-else condition , conditon is true

        let a=5;
        let b=10;
        if(a<b){
            document.write("hi divya","<br>")
        }else{
        document.write("hi nandu","<br>")
        }

O/P : hi divya

EX : IF-else condition , conditon is false

        let a=5;
        let b=10;
        if(a>b){
            document.write("hi divya","<br>")
        }else{
        document.write("hi nandu","<br>")
        }

O/P : hi nandu

EX: else - if

       age=prompt("enter your age?")
        name=prompt("enter your name?")
        if(age<18){
            alert(name + " you are too young to marry")
        }else if (age>35){
            alert(name + "you are too old to marry")
        }else{
            alert(name + " you are perfect to marry")
        }

O/P : <18 - >35 : you are perfect to marry




